# Third-Party Licenses

This file reproduces the full license texts of third-party software statically
linked into msl's distributed binaries — the Swift host binary (`msl`) and the
Rust guest binaries (`msl-agent`, `mac`/msl-shim, `msl-way`). It also records
license metadata for third-party assets distributed with msl. It is a
belt-and-suspenders companion to NOTICE, which gives the short-form summary.
See NOTICE and docs/decisions/0007-licensing.md for the project's overall
licensing posture (msl itself is Apache-2.0).

The app icon includes a transformed copy of Tux:

- Source: https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?curid=753970
- Attribution: By Larry Ewing, Simon Budig, Garrett LeSage -
  https://isc.tamu.edu/~lewing/linux/,
  http://www.home.unix-ag.org/simon/penguin/, garrett/Tux on GitHub
- License: CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication
  (https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)

Regeneration command (guest workspace's Rust dependency section only — the
libxkbcommon and swift-argument-parser sections below are reproduced from
their upstream source and are not cargo-about's concern):

```sh
cd guest
cargo about generate -m Cargo.toml -c about.toml --workspace \
  --target aarch64-unknown-linux-musl --locked --fail \
  ../tools/third-party-licenses.hbs -o /tmp/third-party-rust.md
```


The output of that command is appended verbatim below (see "Rust
dependencies" section). See docs/reports/notice-inventory.md for the exact
end-to-end regeneration steps including the two non-cargo entries.

